offence contravened the provisions of sections 287, 350 and 314 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State. Magistrate J.A. Adegun admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N100,000 with two sureties in like sum. Adegun adjourned the case until Feb. 22 for mention. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria A 32-year-old businessman, Chinedu Okoye, who allegedly obtained N14 million from a man to solve his ”spiritual problems”, on Monday appeared in an Igbosere Magistrates’ Court, Lagos. September 16, 2019 In "News" A 55-year-old trader, Anderson Umeh, who allegedly defrauded a man, Mr Isiah Inaremien of N400,000 under false pretences of getting customs’ paper for his car,  on Monday appeared before an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court. The man, who resides at No. 1b, Kolex Road, Surulere, Lagos, was in court charged with… January 6, 2020 In "Metro" An Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos on Friday ordered that a 51-year-old man, Ukapi Agwu, who allegedly defiled a 13-year-old girl, be remanded in prison. May 19, 2019 In "News"